<HEADLINE> Armed robbery disrupts party at downtown restaurant  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   ALBANY, N.Y. (AP) -- A party of University at Albany graduates
was evacuated from a downtown restaurant Sunday as police searched
for an armed robber who got away with an estimated $40,000.
</P>
<P>
   Police say the robber, described as a black male, 5'4'' tall and
20 years old, approached an employee as she entered the third floor
business office of Jillian's, a restaurant and bar.
</P>
<P>
   The robber reportedly pointed a small caliber gun at the woman,
who complied with his demand to open the safe. Police say the
robber then tied the woman's hands behinds her back and taped her
upper body to a chair before escaping.
</P>
<P>
   Police Sunday were looking for the suspect, last seen wearing a
yellow windbreaker and jeans.
