<HEADLINE> Dow Gains 27; Nasdaq Barely Changed  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- The Dow Jones industrial average is up 27 points
in today's early going. Advancing issues on the New York Stock
Exchange hold a 3-2 lead over decliners.
</P>
<P>
   The Nasdaq Composite Index is virtually unchanged and the
Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 Stock Index is up two points.
</P>
<P>
   Wall Street looks like it's seeing some bargain-hunting to start
the trading week after a dreadful finish to last week.
</P>
<P>
   The market suffered widespread losses Friday with the Nasdaq
composite index down more than four percent.
</P>
<P>
   But with little news to focus on, analysts say it's possible the
continuing fears of higher interest rates could discount any gains
from the market's early bottom fishing.
</P>
<P>
   Stocks have been mostly lower overseas, as measured by the
popular averages in Asia and Europe.
</P>
<P>
   Bond prices are modestly higher.
</P>
