<HEADLINE> Nasdaq Down 207 at Low For Year  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- The Nasdaq composite index fell more than 200
points in early trading Monday to its low point for the year as
investors sold technology stocks on fears that earnings will be
hurt by rising interest rates.
</P>
<P>
   In the first hour of trading, the Nasdaq was down 207.17 at
3,183.23, well below its lowest close of the year --3,321.29 on
April 14, when the index sustained a devastating 355.49-point drop.
</P>
<P>
   The Dow Jones industrial average also was down sharply in early
trading, falling 173.40 to 10,453.45.
</P>
<P>
   Analysts said investors appear to have determined that with
interest rates on the rise, the high price of technology stocks may
not be justified by their earnings.
</P>
<P>
   Last week, the Federal Reserve raised rates for the sixth time
since last June. Recent economic reports have offered a mixed
picture about whether the Fed's rate increases are successfully
slowing the economy. The next major report isn't released until
Thursday, when the Commerce Department issues a preliminary report
on the gross domestic product during the first quarter.
</P>
<P>
   With no positive economic news, many investors were either
selling or staying out of the market. Volume was relatively light.
</P>
<P>
   ------
