<HEADLINE> Japan Royal Couple Visit Geneva  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   GENEVA (AP) -- Emperor Akihito and Empress Michiko of Japan paid
a visit Monday to the International Committee of the Red Cross as
they wrapped up the Swiss leg of their four-country European tour.
</P>
<P>
   Surrounded by vases and a plate given to international Red Cross
leaders by previous Japanese emperors, the imperial couple signed
the visitors' book at ICRC headquarters in traditional Japanese
calligraphy.
</P>
