<HEADLINE> Brewers Sends Estrada To Triple-A  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MILWAUKEE (AP) -- The Milwaukee Brewers sent left-handed pitcher
Horacio Estrada back to Triple-A Indianapolis on Monday and
recalled left-hander Rafael Roque.
</P>
<P>
   Estrada started three games for the Brewers and made two relief
appearances. He was 2-0 with an 8.04 ERA.
</P>
<P>
   On Sunday, Estrada appeared in relief and finally stopped the
San Francisco Giants' 11-run sixth inning before getting his first
major league hit an inning later.
</P>
<P>
   Estrada lost his rotation spot with the returns of injured
starters Jeff D'Amico, John Snyder and Jamey Wright, all of whom
will be in the Brewers' rotation by Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   Roque, the Brewers' opening-day starter in 1999, is back in
Milwaukee's bullpen for the first time this season.
</P>
<P>
   The Brewers will need to make another roster move on Tuesday to
clear a spot for Wright, who is scheduled to make his Milwaukee
debut that day against the Atlanta Braves.
</P>
