<HEADLINE> Big Movers in the Stock Market  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks that moved substantially or traded
heavily Monday on the New York Stock Exchange and Nasdaq Stock
Market.
</P>
<P>
NYSE
</P>
<P>
General Motors, down 9 9/16 at 77]
General Motors Class H shares, up 6~ at 96}
</P>
<P>
   The company is allowing shareholders to swap stock for shares in
Hughes Electronics, a wholly owned subsidiary. The deal is
ultimately expected to boost GM's stock price, and will reduce the
number of GM shares on the market, driving GM's earnings per share
higher.
</P>
<P>
Ryerson Tull Inc., down 4 5/16 at 9 7/16
</P>
<P>
   The company expects the second quarter to be just slightly
profitable. Analysts had predicted Ryerson Tull would earn 49 cents
a share in the quarter. The company, a metals processor, said it
plans to adjust production schedules and inventory.
</P>
<P>
Castle &AMP; Cooke Inc., up 1 3/16 at 18\
</P>
<P>
   A buyout firm run by Castle &AMP; Cooke's chairman and chief
executive agreed to buy the 73 percent of Castle &AMP; Cooke it does
not already own for $18.50 a share, or $230.9 million. Castle &AMP;
Cooke develops commercial and residential real estate in Hawaii.
</P>
<P>
NASDAQ
</P>
<P>
U.S.-China Industrial Exchange, up 4{ at 22{
</P>
<P>
   Shares rose on hopes that the U.S. will sign a permanent trade
agreement with China. The company provides distribution services to
multinational companies and runs a private hospital corporation in
China.
</P>
<P>
Brocade Communications Systems Inc., down 15/16 at 109 5/16
</P>
<P>
   U.S. Bancorp Piper Jaffray lowered its rating on the stock to
''neutral'' from ''buy.'' Brocade makes switches that allow for
quicker transmission of data between computer and storage systems.
</P>
<P>
Vignette Corp., down 8 15/16 at 34~
</P>
<P>
   The company plans to merge with another software company,
OnDisplay Inc., in a stock swap executives say is worth about $1.7
billion. Both companies make software for electronic commerce and
Web site management.
</P>
<P>
Performance Technologies Inc., down 16 13/16 at 11 7/16
</P>
<P>
   The communications equipment maker warned it will miss
second-quarter profit estimates because of a significant order
delay. The company expects to report earnings of 11 cents a share,
compared to analysts' estimates of 19 cents a share.
</P>
</TEXT>
