<BODY>
<HEADLINE> D.C. United Sign Pete Marino  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   HERNDON, Va. (AP) -- Off to their worst start in franchise
history, D.C. United signed forward Pete Marino on Monday to boost
their struggling scoring attack.
</P>
<P>
   Marino has scored 21 goals over four MLS seasons with Columbus,
Kansas City and Tampa Bay, but 11 of those came in his first season
with Columbus in 1996. He was waived by Tampa Bay in March.
</P>
<P>
   United, the three-time MLS champion, are 2-9-1 and in last place
in the Eastern Division, but they have dominated recent games
without putting the ball in the net. The team had to trade prolific
scorer Roy Lassiter last year for salary cap reasons, and Jaime
Moreno is the only United forward who has scored this season.
</P>
<P>
   Marino is expected to play in Saturday's home game against
Dallas.
</P>
<P>
   United also announced that Englishman Michael Blackwood will
join the team next week on a trial basis. The 19-year-old
midfielder played on Aston Villa's reserve squad in England last
season.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
