<HEADLINE> Pitcher Lorraine Signs With Indians  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   CHICAGO (AP) -- Pitcher Andrew Lorraine, cut by the Chicago Cubs
earlier this month, signed a minor league contract with the
Cleveland Indians on Monday.
</P>
<P>
   The 27-year-old lefty went 1-2 with a 6.47 ERA in eight games
for the Cubs. He was assigned to Triple-A Buffalo.
</P>
<P>
   Lorraine was released by the Cubs on May 11 and cleared waivers.
Last season with the Cubs, he went 2-5 with two complete games,
including a three-hit shutout of Houston.
</P>
<P>
   Lorraine has a 6-10 major league record and has also pitched
with the Angels, White Sox, Athletics and Mariners.
</P>
