<HEADLINE> Stanford's Irvin Defeats Faucher  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MALIBU, Calif. (AP) -- Top-seeded Marissa Irvin of Stanford
defeated Michelle Faucher of Texas 6-3, 1-6, 6-2 in the first round
of NCAA tournament singles play at Pepperdine on Monday.
</P>
<P>
   Irvin rallied in the third set to avoid an upset loss.
</P>
<P>
   ''I started out the match well and then had a mental lapse in
the second set,'' Irvin said. ''It is always tough to win in the
first round, especially after losing in the team championship
yesterday.''
</P>
<P>
   Georgia, which defeated top-ranked Stanford to win the team
title Sunday 5-4, was represented by four players in the singles
draw and each of the Lady Bulldogs advanced. Georgia's Aarthi
Venkatesan, the No. 5 seed, defeated Arizona's Lindsay Blau by
scores of 6-2, 6-0.
</P>
<P>
   Janet Walker of Texas, the No. 2 seed, lost 3-6, 6-2, 6-3 to
Megan Payne-Dorny of Utah, while third-seeded Adria Engel of Wake
Forest was upset by Stephanie Hazlett of Florida 6-4, 6-2.
</P>
<P>
   Zuzana Lesenarova of San Diego, the No. 4 seed and defending
NCAA singles champion, posted a 6-2, 6-4 first round victory over
Maureen Diaz of UC Irvine.
</P>
<P>
   ''It feels good to get the first win of the tournament,''
Lesenarova said. ''That burden is out of my head and now I can
focus on the rest of the tournament.''
</P>
<P>
   No. 8 Megan Miller of Duke lost 7-5, 6-4 to Annica Cooper of
UCLA.
</P>
<P>
   Stanford had five players in the singles draw, but Lauren
Kalvaria and Keiko Tokuda both lost three-set matches. Stanford's
Laura Granville defeated Vladka Uhlirova of Texas 6-2, 6-2, while
Teryn Ashley beat Kristi Dascoli of Ohio State 6-4, 6-2.
</P>
<P>
   The tournament continues Tuesday with second- and third-round
women's singles matches.
</P>
